Current status

Model development is in progress

A study was conducted to define the balance threshold for classifying a customer as HNWI. The initial threshold of UAH 1,000,000 resulted in a very small training sample.

To increase the number of observations, several lower thresholds were tested:

UAH 300K: 119 HNWI clients — 38.64%
UAH 500K: 72 HNWI clients — 23.38%
UAH 700K: 52 HNWI clients — 16.88%
UAH 1M: 46 HNWI clients — 14.94%

Based on this analysis, UAH 700,000 was selected as the working HNWI threshold. It provides a larger training sample while preserving a relatively high customer wealth level.

The model is currently being developed and tested.

